The paper discusses the optimization of deep neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. Specifically, the paper focuses on designing low-precision DNNs with good generalization capability, which is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) applications. The proposed approach involves model averaging, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) to improve the generalization capability of models. The paper also discusses the use of cyclical learning rates, which is a technique commonly used in neural network optimization (cs.NE) to improve the convergence of models. Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the proposed approach in VLSI or low-precision neural processing units, which is relevant to the field of computer architecture (cs.AR).
